Steps for Install tensorFlow library on ubuntu after Anaconda installation:

1) Set path of conda: export PATH=~/anaconda3/bin:$PATH
2) Create the environment: conda create -n tensorflow python=3.6 pip
3) Start the environment: source activate tensorflow
4) Install the matplotlib using conda: conda install -c conda-forge matplotlib
5) Install the tensorflow: pip install --ignore-installed --upgrade \https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/linux/cpu/tensorflow-1.5.0-cp36-cp36m-linux_x86_64.whl
6) Start anaconda: anaconda-navigator